<h1>GitHub Use Policy</h1>
<p>When you connect your GitHub account to your SWAMP account, you are asking SWAMP to rely on the security of your GitHub account.  You are responsible for protecting your GitHub account with a <a style="cursor: pointer" data-toggle="popover" data-placement="right" title="SWAMP Password Policy" data-content="<%= passwordPolicy %>">strong password</a>. SWAMP also recommends enabling <a target="_blank" href="https://help.github.com/articles/about-two-factor-authentication">GitHub two factor authentication</a>.</p>

<h2>Statement of Agreement</h2>
<p>If you accept this responsibility, click "I accept" then click "Sign Up!" to create and link a new SWAMP acccount with GitHub, or "Link Existing" if you already have a SWAMP account and you'd like to link it to your GitHub account. If you have questions, please contact the Help Desk at <code><a href="mailto:support@continuousassurance.org">support@continuousassurance.org</a></code>.</p>

<div class="alert alert-warning" style="display:none">
	<button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert"><i class="fa fa-close"></i></button>
	<label>Warning: </label><span class="message">This form contains errors.  Please correct and resubmit.</span>
</div>

<form action="/" id="accept-form">
	<div class="well">
		<label class="required">
			I accept
			<input type="checkbox" name="accept" id="accept" class="required" />
		</label>
	</div>
</form>

<p>
If you are <b>new to the SWAMP</b>, please click Sign Up to complete your registration. If you are an <b>existing SWAMP user</b>, please click Link Existing to connect your GitHub account to your SWAMP account so you can sign in via GitHub in the future.
</p>

<div class="bottom buttons">
	<button id="register-new" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary"><i class="fa fa-pencil"></i>Sign Up</button> 
	<button id="link-existing" class="btn btn-lg"><i class="fa fa-link"></i>Link Existing</button>
</div>